[The specific hantavirus involved in these 3 cases, or those in 2012, are not given. In the lowland Amazon Basin of Bolivia, the possible hantavirus, its rodent hosts, and their images that might be involved in these hantavirus pulmonary syndrome (HPS) cases is Laguna Negra virus (_Calomys laucha_ http://www.faunaparaguay.com/images/Calomys%20laucha%20enciso%2031aug2011.jpg and _C. callosus_ https://eee.uci.edu/clients/bjbecker/PlaguesandPeople/Calomyscallosusb.jpg). Other hantaviruses and their rodent hosts that have been found in lowland Bolivia and can cause HPS include:
- Bermejo (_Oligoryzomys chacoensis_ http://guidetomammals.blog.com/files/2012/05/Oligoryzomys-chacoensis.jpg), and
- Oran (_O. longicaudatus_ http://calphotos.berkeley.edu/imgs/512x768/0000_0000/0711/1203.jpeg

Maps of Bolivia can be accessed at http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/bolivia_admin_2006.jpg and http://healthmap.org/r/52sz. - Mod.TY]
